{% doc %}
  @prompt
    # Slideshow Section Specification
    
    ## Overview
    Create a responsive slideshow section optimized for both desktop and mobile devices.  
    Each slide supports independent image uploads, customizable text overlays, and flexible button placement.
    
    ---
    
    ## Features
    
    ### 1. Device-Specific Image Settings
    - Separate image uploads for **mobile** and **desktop**
    - Automatically switches between images based on screen size
    
    ### 2. Text Overlay Configuration
    - Adjustable text positioning: **top / center / bottom × left / center / right**
    - Customizable text color
    
    ### 3. Button Configuration
    - Customizable **button text** and **link URL**
    - Adjustable button positioning: **top / center / bottom × left / center / right**
    - Customizable button color
    
    ### 4. Slide Management
    - Support for **multiple slides**
    - Ability to **add or remove** slides
    
    ### 5. Animation & Navigation
    - Smooth slide transitions
    - Navigation **arrows** and **dots** for slide control
    
    ### 6. Layout & Size Settings
    #### Height Options
    - 0～100vh (full viewport height)  ※Custom　Values
    - Custom pixel values  
    - Percentage-based values  
    - Separate height settings for **mobile** and **desktop**
    
    #### Width Options
    - 100% (full width)  
    - Custom percentage values  
    - Max-width constraints
    
    ### 7. Design Style
    - Full-width **hero banner layout**
    - Images use `object-fit: cover` to maintain aspect ratio and visual consistency
    
    ---
    
    ## Use Cases
    - Homepage **hero slider**
    - **Campaign** or **landing page** visual sections
    - Category-based **product showcase sliders**
    
    ---
    
    ## Implementation Notes
    This specification can be implemented as a **Shopify section**, or with a **custom HTML/CSS/Swiper.js** setup.  
    Code templates (Liquid / HTML / JS / CSS) can be generated upon request.
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  .ai-slideshow-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    position: relative;
    width: {{ block.settings.width }}%;
    max-width: {{ block.settings.max_width }}px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.border_radius }}px;
  }

  .ai-slideshow-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    position: relative;
    height: {{ block.settings.height_desktop }}vh;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .ai-slideshow-track-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: flex;
    transition: transform 0.5s ease-in-out;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .ai-slide-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    min-width: 100%;
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .ai-slide-image-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .ai-slide-content-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    padding: 40px;
    text-align: center;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
  }

  .ai-slide-text-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .ai-slide-heading-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.heading_size }}px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ai-slide-text-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-size: {{ block.settings.text_size }}px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ai-slide-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.button_color }};
    color: {{ block.settings.button_text_color }};
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.button_border_radius }}px;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .ai-slide-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
    background-color: {{ block.settings.button_hover_color }};
    color: {{ block.settings.button_hover_text_color }};
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

